com.ibm.team.repository.common.validation

Interface IPropertyConstraintErrorStatus

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IStatus
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IStringSizeConstraintErrorStatus

    public interface IPropertyConstraintErrorStatus
extends org.eclipse.core.runtime.IStatus
    Base type for any validation error generated by IItemValidator. Status codes are defined in constants, and additional meta info can be introspected from the error status, by casting to this interface.
    Since:
    0.6
    See Also:
    IItemValidator

    • Method Detail

      • getRootType

        IItemType getRootType()
        Answers the item type for the top-level Item being validated. This may be null if a request was made to simply validate a helper property using IType#validatePropertyStringSize(String, String)
        Returns:
        the item type for the top-level Item being validated

      • getOwnerType

        IType getOwnerType()
        Answers the type (IItemType | IHelperType) that is the owning type for the invalid property. This will be the same as getRootType() if the property is on a top-level item.
        Returns:
        the type that is the owning type for the invalid property; never null

      • getPropertyPath

        java.lang.String[] getPropertyPath()
        Answers the path from the root item type to the property that failed validation. The path is an array of Strings, where dynamic gets from a root item to the children leads to the invalid property. If the request was made to simply validate a helper property using IItemValidator.validateAttribute(IType, String, Object) then the path will only contain the single property name.
        Returns:
        an array of Strings; never null
